Reasoning: The paper is about developing an algorithmic theory of brain networks based on stochastic Spiking Neural Network (SNN) models. This falls under the category of neural networks and artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.NE. The paper also discusses problems of similarity detection and neural coding, which are topics in machine learning and pattern recognition, covered by cs.AI. The composition and hiding operators discussed in the paper are related to the field of control theory, which is covered by cs.SY. The paper also discusses building circuits and networks, which falls under the category of computer architecture and digital circuits, covered by cs.CC. Finally, the paper discusses external behavior notions and requirements for SNNs, which is related to the field of formal methods and verification, covered by cs.LG.
